          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "enable": true,
            "content": "<p>Gifting sweet treats in warmer weather takes a little extra care. <strong>Chocolate, caramels, and gelatin-based gummies</strong> are heat-sensitive and may melt or lose their shape when temperatures rise above 75°F. Even with fast shipping, a gift may spend time in a warm delivery truck or be left outside on a sunny porch. </p><p>To help preserve the quality of the gift, we offer an optional insulated shipping upgrade that includes:</p><ul><li>A cold pack to help maintain a safe temperature</li><li>An insulated thermal liner for longer-lasting protection</li><li>Greater peace of mind that the gift will arrive in great condition</li></ul><p>This upgrade is highly recommended when shipping to warmer climates or during hot seasons — especially in states like California, Texas, Florida, Arizona, or the Southeast.</p>"
          }
        },
